        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 30 at 4:15PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 414 PM EDT, National Weather Service doppler radar indicated a
line of strong thunderstorms near Norwood, or near Warrenton,
moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, pea sized hail, frequent cloud to
ground lightning and increased chance of a brief tornado.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...While winds should result in minor damage to tree limbs
and blowing around of light, unsecured objects, this
line of storms has also exhibited localized rotation. A
brief tornado could quickly form.

Locations impacted include...
Warrenton, Norwood, Camak, Powelton, and Mesena.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 800 PM EDT for
east central Georgia.</instruction>
